subSubSection.paragraph:
Spicules.
Megascleres (
Fig. 1
C–L; 
Table 1
) are strongyles, larger spicules slightly sinuously curved, slightly thinner at one end (
Fig. 1
C–E), smaller spicules sharply bent proximally (
Fig. 1F, G
), with faint tylote (
Fig. 1C, E, J
), centrotylote (
Fig. 1L
), and ‘shepherd’s crook’ (
Fig. 1H, I
) modifications: 398 (230–539) µm long, 8 (5–12) µm wide, n = 30.

